# Copy to env/web.env and point at your backend's reachable address.
# Same shared env/ directory convention as env/server.env — local (non-Docker)
# dev and `vite build`/`vite dev` both read env/web.env via a dotenv.config()
# call at the top of apps/web/vite.config.ts (Vite has no built-in way to point
# its own .env loading at a directory outside the app root).
#
# Must be prefixed VITE_ to be readable from app code (Vite inlines only
# VITE_* vars into the client bundle).
#
# Unlike the server's MONGO_URI, this is the *same* value for local (non-Docker)
# dev and docker compose — it's read by the browser, not container-to-container,
# so it's always "localhost:3000" (the server's host-mapped port), never the
# internal compose service name "server":
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
# Only relevant for the Docker image build (docker/web.Dockerfile) — same value,
# passed as a --build-arg instead, since it's inlined at build time, not read
# from this file inside the container (see docker/docker-compose.yml's web
# service and apps/web/README.md's "Production build & Docker" section):
#   docker build --build-arg VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000 ...
